{{Infobox person | name = Josephine Bornebusch | image = Josephine Bornebusch -2.jpg | alt = | caption = Josephine Bornebusch (2013) | birth_name = Leyla Jerrie Josephine Bornebusch | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1981|9|12|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Stockholm]], Sweden | nationality = | other_names = | known_for = | occupation = Actress | children = 1 }}
'''Leyla Jerrie Josephine Bornebusch''' (born 12 September 1981) is a [[Swedes|Swedish]] actress. She began her acting career in the Swedish drama series ''[[Rederiet]]'' in 1999 and a year later she starred alongside [[Alexander Skarsgård]] in the films ''[[White Water Fury]]'' and ''[[Wings of Glass]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.expressen.se/noje/extra/sa-gick-det-for-skadespelarna-i-rederiet/ |title=Så gick det för skådespelarna i Rederiet &#124; Extra &#124; Expressen |publisher=Expressen.se |date=2010-04-01 |accessdate=2014-07-06}}</ref><ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite web|url=http://www.nbc.com/welcome-to-sweden/about/bio/josephine-bornebusch |title=Josephine Bornebusch |publisher=NBC |date=2014-06-17 |accessdate=2014-07-06}}</ref> In 2002 Bornebusch again acted in a film alongside Skarsgård as one of the lead roles of the film ''[[The Dog Trick]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.svd.se/kultur/film/hundtricket-gar-hem_23068.svd |title= Hundtricket går hem|publisher=Svenska Dagbladet |date=|accessdate=2014-07-08}}</ref> She was an actor in the comedy show ''[[Playa del Sol]]'' on [[SVT1]].<ref name="deadline1">{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/08/paradigm-signs-swedish-comedy-star-josephine-bornebusch/ |title=Paradigm Signs Swedish Comedy Star Josephine Bornebusch |publisher=Deadline.com |date=2013-08-23 |accessdate=2014-07-06}}</ref> She was also one of the regular hosts of ''[[Fredag Hela Veckan]]'', a Swedish version of ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''. She has starred as "Mickan" in the comedy series ''[[Solsidan (TV series)|Solsidan]]''.<ref name="deadline1"/>
Bornebusch is a writer, associate producer, and female lead opposite [[Greg Poehler]] in ''[[Welcome to Sweden (2014 TV series)|Welcome to Sweden]]'' which was broadcast on [[TV4 (Sweden)|TV4]] in Sweden and on [[NBC]] in the United States.<ref name="autogenerated1"/> The series was cancelled on 28 July 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/nbc-cancels-welcome-sweden-811682|title = NBC Cancels 'Welcome to Sweden'|date = 28 July 2015|accessdate = 3 August 2015|website = [[The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher = |last = Goldberg|first = Lesley}}</ref>
In July 2014 Bornebusch revealed that she was pregnant with her first child.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/nojesbladet/article19165369.ab |title=Josephine Bornebusch är gravid &#124; Nöjesbladet &#124; Aftonbladet |publisher=Aftonbladet.se |date=2014-07-01 |accessdate=2014-07-06}}</ref> In late August of the same year she gave birth to a son.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.expressen.se/noje/josephine-bornebusch-har-blivit-mamma/|title=Josephine Bornebusch har blivit mamma|work=Expressen|accessdate=20 September 2014}}</ref>
